<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="160" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,356,815]" pageId="3" pageNumber="160">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,391,416]" pageId="3" pageNumber="160">Comments</emphasis>
. This species was previously known only from 
<collectingCountry box="[887,1002,391,416]" name="Venezuela" pageId="3" pageNumber="160">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Spencer" box="[1019,1193,392,416]" pageId="3" pageNumber="160" refString="Spencer, K. A. (1973 a) The Agromyzidae of Venezuela. Revista de la Facultad de Agronomia (Maracay), 7 (2), 5 - 107." type="journal article" year="1973" yearSuffix="a">
Spencer 
<number box="[1121,1180,392,416]" pageId="3" pageNumber="160" value="1973.0">1973</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Martinez" pageId="3" pageNumber="160" refString="Martinez, M. &amp; Etienne, J. (2002) Liste systematique et biogeographique des Agromyzidae (Diptera) de la region neotropicale. Bolletino di Zoologia agraria e di Bachicoltura, Serie II, 34, 25 - 52." type="journal article" year="2002">
Martinez &amp; Etienne 
<number box="[151,212,428,452]" pageId="3" pageNumber="160" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Externally, the Ecuadorian male specimen mostly agrees with the original description of 
<taxonomicName box="[1262,1436,428,453]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="160" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="memoranda">
<emphasis box="[1262,1436,428,453]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="160">M. memoranda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
except as follows: eye dorsally hairy; antenna not especially large; wing length 
<quantity box="[1063,1151,464,488]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9" pageId="3" pageNumber="160" unit="mm" value="2.9">2.9 mm</quantity>
(compared to 
<quantity box="[1318,1406,464,488]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="3" pageNumber="160" unit="mm" value="2.4">2.4 mm</quantity>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Spencer" box="[151,321,500,524]" pageId="3" pageNumber="160" refString="Spencer, K. A. (1973 a) The Agromyzidae of Venezuela. Revista de la Facultad de Agronomia (Maracay), 7 (2), 5 - 107." type="journal article" year="1973" yearSuffix="a">
Spencer 
<number box="[248,307,500,524]" pageId="3" pageNumber="160" value="1973.0">1973</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
); last section of CuA 
<number box="[558,566,515,529]" pageId="3" pageNumber="160" value="1.0">1</number>
about 
<number box="[642,691,500,525]" pageId="3" pageNumber="160" value="0.5">0.50</number>
length of penultimate. Other notable characters not in the original description are the narrow sub-shining orbit, each of which is about 
<number box="[936,985,538,563]" pageId="3" pageNumber="160" value="0.15">0.15</number>
times the width of the frons (including orbits) and the long orbital setulae in two rows, with the outer row reclinate and the inner row mostly erect. The phallus of the Ecuadorian specimen (
<figureCitation box="[590,701,610,635]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1512,1535]" captionTargetBox="[336,1250,877,1485]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[326,1260,870,1491]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 9. Melanagromyza memoranda Spencer, (7) phallus, lateral, (8) phallus, ventral, (9) hypandrium and epandrium, arrow shows small epandrial spine. Scale bars = 0.05 mm except Fig. 9 = 0.01 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252254/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="160">
Figs. 
<number box="[658,701,611,635]" pageId="3" pageNumber="160" value="7.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="7.0">7–8</number>
</figureCitation>
) matches the original illustrations of 
<taxonomicName box="[1148,1324,610,635]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="160" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="memoranda">
<emphasis box="[1148,1324,610,635]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="160">M. memoranda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Spencer" pageId="3" pageNumber="160" refString="Spencer, K. A. (1973 a) The Agromyzidae of Venezuela. Revista de la Facultad de Agronomia (Maracay), 7 (2), 5 - 107." type="journal article" year="1973" yearSuffix="a">
Spencer 
<number box="[151,210,647,671]" pageId="3" pageNumber="160" value="1973.0">1973</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
), with the U-shaped basiphallus more clearly visible in a freshly dissected specimen (
<figureCitation box="[1183,1252,646,671]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1512,1535]" captionTargetBox="[336,1250,877,1485]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[326,1260,870,1491]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 9. Melanagromyza memoranda Spencer, (7) phallus, lateral, (8) phallus, ventral, (9) hypandrium and epandrium, arrow shows small epandrial spine. Scale bars = 0.05 mm except Fig. 9 = 0.01 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252254/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="160">
Fig. 
<number box="[1236,1252,647,671]" pageId="3" pageNumber="160" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
, inset) (possibly due to chemical treatment). This species also has a characteristic extended hypandrial apodeme (
<figureCitation box="[1293,1366,682,707]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1512,1535]" captionTargetBox="[336,1250,877,1485]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[326,1260,870,1491]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 9. Melanagromyza memoranda Spencer, (7) phallus, lateral, (8) phallus, ventral, (9) hypandrium and epandrium, arrow shows small epandrial spine. Scale bars = 0.05 mm except Fig. 9 = 0.01 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252254/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="160">
Fig. 
<number box="[1350,1366,683,707]" pageId="3" pageNumber="160" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
). The epandrium has multiple small spines internally with 
<number box="[735,778,718,743]" pageId="3" pageNumber="160" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6</number>
longer ones, and one small spine at the hind corner (arrow, 
<figureCitation box="[151,220,754,779]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1512,1535]" captionTargetBox="[336,1250,877,1485]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[326,1260,870,1491]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 9. Melanagromyza memoranda Spencer, (7) phallus, lateral, (8) phallus, ventral, (9) hypandrium and epandrium, arrow shows small epandrial spine. Scale bars = 0.05 mm except Fig. 9 = 0.01 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252254/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="160">
Fig. 
<number box="[204,220,755,779]" pageId="3" pageNumber="160" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
). The Brazilian species 
<taxonomicName authority="Braun and Prado (Braun et al. 2009)" authorityName="Braun and Prado (Braun et al." authorityYear="2009" box="[494,1078,754,779]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="160" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falciformis">
<emphasis box="[494,653,754,779]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="160">M. falciformis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[662,1078,754,779]" pageId="3" pageNumber="160" refString="Braun, M. R., Prado, A. P. &amp; Lewinsohn, T. M. (2009) New species of Neotropical Melanagromyza Hendel (Diptera: Agromyzidae) from Asteraceae flower heads. Zootaxa, 2279, 51 - 59." type="journal article">
Braun and Prado (Braun 
<emphasis box="[947,997,754,779]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="160">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[1012,1070,755,779]" pageId="3" pageNumber="160" value="2009.0">2009</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
has somewhat similar genitalia but that species is much smaller, with a wing length not exceeding 
<quantity box="[900,1000,791,815]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.28" pageId="3" pageNumber="160" unit="mm" value="1.28">1.28 mm</quantity>
in the male.
</paragraph>
